&gt; Cherry-picking a single best population, one of many. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Wouldn&#39;t this be akin to an island model without migration?&nbsp; Such puncuated equilibrium systems have shown to be useful but typically inclusion of migration is very helpful.&nbsp; This also begins to dip into speciation but holds a forced separation of populations rather than a similarity-based separation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Kirk&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote style=&quot;border-left: 2px solid rgb(0, 0, 255); padding-left: 5px; margin-left: 0px;&quot;&gt;-----Original Message-----
